latestPosts.caption:
My dearest body, thank you. You’ve changed in ways I never expected. Softer in places, marked by time and love. Every change tells the story of the two beautiful lives you carried. You’ve stretched, ached, and endured more than I thought possible, yet through it all, you held me steady. You were the home where my children began, and for that, I will always be in awe of you.
You don’t look like you used to, but you don’t feel like you used to either. You feel stronger, fuller, wiser. My heart has tripled in size, filled with a love I never knew existed, and it’s because of you. I promise to treat you with the gentleness and gratitude you deserve, to see you not through the lens of loss, but through the miracle of all that you’ve given me. ❤️
